</H2>
<UL>
<LI>If R is decomposed into X, Y and Z, and we enforce the FDs that hold on X, on Y and on Z, then all FDs that were given to hold on R must also hold.  (Avoids Problem (3).)
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Projection of set of FDs F:   If R is decomposed into X, ... projection of F onto X  (denoted FX ) is the set of FDs U       V in F+ (closure of F ) such that U, V are in X. </H2>
</UL></P>
